Transfer Conversations with the Set Routing Type Dialog Step

Use the Set Routing Type dialog step to route enhanced bot conversations to a different outbound Omni-Channel flow than the default outbound Omni-Channel flow. To route conversations from the Transfer to Agent dialog or the Transfer to Agent Next Step, use the Outbound Omni-Channel Flow setting instead.

Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
To use enhanced Messaging channels with Enhanced Bots, view required editions.


To build and manage Einstein Bots:

Customize Application

OR

Modify Metadata

OR

Manage Bots


Before you begin, create an Omni-Channel flow for your transfer use case.
In the Bot Builder menu, select Variables and click New. For the Data Type, select ID. For the SObject Type, select Omni-Channel Flow. Save your changes.
Create a Set Routing Type dialog step with the same flow ID variable to initiate the transfer.
In the Step Properties panel, complete these fields:
Route Type - Select Omni-Channel Flow
Route Destination - Select the Omni-Channel flow to use to transfer the conversation
Destination Variable - Select the ID variable that you created

All conversations that arenâ€™t routed go to the No Agent Available dialog.
